decks.notes: Sythis, Harvest's Hand is a control deck focused on utilizing enchantments to establish board control and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck includes a variety of enchantress effects to draw cards and generate value, while also running hate enchantments like Absolute Grace and Absolute Law to protect itself. The deck aims to ramp up its mana production with cards like Utopia Sprawl and Fertile Ground, allowing it to deploy threats like Eidolon of Blossoms and Parallax Wave efficiently. Sythis, Harvest's Hand synergizes with enchantress abilities and can quickly overwhelm opponents with a board full of powerful enchantments, making it a formidable control deck in the Duel Commander format.

This deck focuses on utilizing the Goblin tribal synergies to quickly ramp up mana and flood the board with aggressive creatures. The goal is to efficiently cast Muxus, Goblin Grandee and take advantage of his ability to cheat goblins into play from the top of the library, overwhelming the opponent with a high number of creatures and dealing damage quickly. Rituals and mana acceleration spells help to cast Muxus early, while the variety of goblins provide additional support and utility to maintain board presence and push for lethal damage. The inclusion of cards like Kiki-Jiki, Mirror Breaker adds a combo element for additional win conditions, ensuring multiple paths to victory.
